ss=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003eIt's how quickly and effectively you repair after rupture.\\u003c/strong\\u003e\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",\\\"8\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-2xl font-bold text-white font-serif mt-12 mb-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"The Four Horsemen Are Real — But Incomplete\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"10\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"You've probably heard of Gottman's \\\\\\\"Four Horsemen of the Apocalypse\\\\\\\" — the four communication behaviours that predict relationship failure:\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"15\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"1. \\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003eCriticism\\u003c/strong\\u003e — attacking your partner's character instead of their behaviour\\u003cbr /\\u003e2. \\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003eContempt\\u003c/strong\\u003e — treating your partner with disrespect, mocking, or superiority\\u003cbr /\\u003e3. \\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003eDefensiveness\\u003c/strong\\u003e — deflecting responsibility and counter-attacking\\u003cbr /\\u003e4. \\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003eStonewalling\\u003c/strong\\u003e — withdrawing and refusing to engage\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"17\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"These are real, they're measurable, and their presence is genuinely predictive. Contempt alone is the single strongest predictor of divorce.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"19\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"But here's the piece most people miss: \\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003ethe masters of relationships also display the Four Horsemen.\\u003c/strong\\u003e Not as often, perhaps, but they're there. These couples aren't conflict-free angels floating through life in perfect harmony. They're human beings who get tired, stressed, and reactive — just like everyone else.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"21\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"The difference? They repair. Fast. And effectively.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",\\\"23\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-2xl font-bold text-white font-serif mt-12 mb-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"What Repair Actually Looks Like in the Brain\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"25\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"A repair attempt is any statement or action — verbal or nonverbal — that de-escalates conflict and prevents negative sentiment from spiraling. It can be as simple as:\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"30\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"- A touch on the arm during a tense conversation\\u003cbr /\\u003e- \\\\\\\"I'm sorry, that came out wrong. Let me try again.\\\\\\\"\\u003cbr /\\u003e- A moment of humour that breaks the tension\\u003cbr /\\u003e- \\\\\\\"We're getting off track. I love you. Let's start over.\\\\\\\"\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"32\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"What's happening neurologically during a successful repair is remarkable. The repair bid activates the partner's ventral vagal system — the social engagement circuit — which begins to downregulate the sympathetic activation (fight/flight) that conflict triggered. Heart rate slows. Cortisol begins to clear. The prefrontal cortex comes back online.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"34\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"In essence, a successful repair is one nervous system offering safety to another. It's co-regulation in action. And it is the single most important relationship skill you will ever develop.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",\\\"36\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-2xl font-bold text-white font-serif mt-12 mb-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Why Most Couples Fail at Repair\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"38\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"If repair is so important, why don't more couples do it? Three reasons:\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"40\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"\\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003e1. They don't recognise repair attempts.\\u003c/strong\\u003e Gottman found that in distressed couples, 86% of repair attempts go unrecognised by the receiving partner. A partner might say \\\\\\\"Can we take a break?\\\\\\\" — which is a repair bid — and the other hears it as avoidance. The bid is there. The recognition isn't.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"42\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"\\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003e2. They're too dysregulated to offer repair.\\u003c/strong\\u003e You can't repair from a state of flooding. If both partners are in sympathetic activation — hearts racing, stress hormones surging — neither has the neurological resources to initiate repair. This is why the twenty-minute physiological cool-down is essential. You cannot do the sophisticated social-cognitive work of repair from a dysregulated nervous system.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"44\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"\\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003e3. They carry negative sentiment override.\\u003c/strong\\u003e This is Gottman's term for the perceptual filter that develops in distressed relationships where even neutral or positive bids are interpreted negatively. Your partner brings you coffee. In a healthy relationship, you think \\\\\\\"That's nice.\\\\\\\" In negative sentiment override, you think \\\\\\\"What do they want?\\\\\\\" or \\\\\\\"They're trying to avoid the conversation we need to have.\\\\\\\"\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",\\\"46\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-2xl font-bold text-white font-serif mt-12 mb-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"The 5:1 Ratio\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"48\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Gottman's most famous finding is the \\\\\\\"magic ratio\\\\\\\" — that stable, happy relationships maintain a ratio of at least five positive interactions for every one negative interaction during conflict. Not in daily life — during \\u003cem class=\\\\\\\"text-[#d4af37]/80\\\\\\\"\\u003econflict.\\u003c/em\\u003e\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"50\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"This doesn't mean you need to be artificially positive during arguments. It means that within the natural flow of a disagreement, healthy couples sprinkle in moments of connection, humour, affection, and validation that keep the overall emotional tone from going toxic.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"54\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"\\\\\\\"I hear you, and I disagree, but I see why you feel that way.\\\\\\\"\\u003cbr /\\u003e\\\\\\\"This is hard, but I'm glad we're talking about it.\\\\\\\"\\u003cbr /\\u003e\\\\\\\"You make a fair point about the finances. I still think we need to discuss the timeline.\\\\\\\"\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"56\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Each of these is a positive interaction within a conflict context. And they are the connective tissue that allows a relationship to absorb the inevitable negativity of disagreement without sustaining structural damage.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",\\\"58\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-2xl font-bold text-white font-serif mt-12 mb-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"What Gottman Doesn't Talk About (But I Will)\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"60\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Gottman's research is foundational. I reference it constantly. But there are layers he doesn't address that my work in hypnotherapy and NLP fills in.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"62\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Specifically: \\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003ewhy some people cannot repair even when they know how.\\u003c/strong\\u003e\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"64\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"The answer, in my experience, is subconscious programming. If your implicit memory contains the encoding \\\\\\\"admitting fault means I'm defective\\\\\\\" — usually installed by a critical or shaming caregiver — then the act of repair (which requires vulnerability) feels existentially threatening. Your conscious mind knows you should apologise. Your subconscious blocks it because, in its calculus, the vulnerability of apology is more dangerous than the conflict itself.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"66\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"In hypnotherapy, we can access and rework these encodings. We can help the nervous system learn that vulnerability is not weakness, that repair is not submission, that saying \\\\\\\"I'm sorry, I got it wrong\\\\\\\" does not annihilate the self.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"68\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"In NLP, we use timeline work to locate the original decision point — the moment the subconscious installed the belief — and update it with the resources of the adult self. \\\\\\\"Little me decided that being wrong was dangerous. Adult me knows that being wrong is human, and that repair is the bravest thing I can do in my relationship.\\\\\\\"\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",\\\"70\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-2xl font-bold text-white font-serif mt-12 mb-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"The Practice\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"72\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"This week, practise one repair attempt per conflict. Just one. It doesn't have to be perfect. It doesn't have to resolve everything. It just has to communicate: \\\\\\\"I am choosing this relationship over my need to be right.\\\\\\\"\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"74\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"And if your partner offers a repair bid — even a clumsy, imperfect one — receive it. Let it land. Let it do its neurological work of calming your nervous system and restoring the connection between you.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"76\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Repair is not about being the bigger person. It's about being the braver one. And in my experience, the couples who make it are the ones who get brave on a regular basis.\\\"}}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L16\\\",null,{\\\"title\\\":\\\"The Gottman Research Most Therapists Ignore\\\",\\\"slug\\\":\\\"the-gottman-research-most-therapists-ignore\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L17\\\",null,{}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"mt-16 rounded-2xl border border-[#d4af37]/30 bg-gradient-to-b from-[#d4af37]/10 to-transparent p-8 text-center\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h3\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-xl font-bold text-white font-serif\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Ready to talk about what you just read?\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"mt-2 text-sm text-[#a0aec0] font-sans max-w-md mx-auto\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Book a free discovery call with Hakeem Lesolang. No pressure. No pitch. Just an honest conversation about where you are and where you want to be.\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"a\\\",null,{\\\"href\\\":\\\"https://calendly.com/folasessions/discovery-call\\\",\\\"target\\\":\\\"_blank\\\",\\\"rel\\\":\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"mt-6 inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-[#d4af37] text-[#1a365d] px-6 py-3 rounded-xl text-sm font-bold font-sans hover:bg-[#e4bf47] transition-all hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-[#d4af37]/20\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"Book Your Free Discovery Call\\\",[\\\"$\\\",\\\"svg\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"w-4 h-4\\\",\\\"fill\\\":\\\"none\\\",\\\"viewBox\\\":\\\"0 0 24 24\\\",\\\"stroke\\\":\\\"currentColor\\\",\\\"strokeWidth\\\":2.5,\\\"children\\\":[\\\"$\\\",\\\"path\\\",null,{\\\"strokeLinecap\\\":\\\"ro